ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport what estimate she has made of the level of local authority funding for (a) the arts and (b) museums in each of the last four years.

reply.p: I refer the hon. Member to the local authority expenditure table on page 218 of the Department's annual report 2001, copies of which are available in the Library of the House. The report can also be accessed via the Department's website at www.culture.gov.uk

ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Health what the proportion was of (a) women and (b) black and Asian non-executive members of health authorities and NHS trusts in May 1997; and what were the proportions appointed in (i) 1997–98, (ii) 1998–99, (iii) 1999–2000 and (iv) 2000–01.

reply.p: The proportions of non-executive directors, including chairs, on the boards of national health service trusts and health authorities for each year since May 1997 who were women, or black or from an ethnic minority background, are shown in the table in percentage terms.
